}s. It is likely based on the {{wp|Panorpidae|scorpionfly}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nGliscor and Glion are a combination of \'\'glide\'\' and \'\'scorpion\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ground|type2=Flying\n|ja=グライオン \'\'Glion\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'glide\'\' and \'\'scorpion\'\'\n|fr=Scorvol|frmeaning=From \'\'scorpion\'\' and \'\'{{tt|vol|flight}}\'\'\n|es=Gliscor|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Skorgro|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Skorpion\'\'|scorpion}} and \'\'{{tt|groß|big}}\'\'\n|it=Gliscor|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=글라이온 \'\'Glion\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of its Japanese name\n|zh_yue=天蠍王 / 天蝎王 \'\'Tīn Hit Wòhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Literally "Sky scorpion king"\n|zh_cmn=天蠍王 / 天蝎王 \'\'Tiān Xiē Wáng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Sky scorpion king"\n|ru=Глискор \'\'Gliskor\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{left clear}}\n\n==Related articles==\n*[[Ash\'s Gliscor]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ground|type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ground|prevnum=471|prev=Glaceon|nextnum=473|next=Mamoswine}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Pokémon with cross-generational evolutions]]\n\n[[de:Skorgro]]\n[[es:Gliscor]]\n[[fr:Scorvol]]\n[[it:Gliscor]]\n[[ja:グライオン]]\n[[zh:天蝎王]]'}